Share with:
Accounting Executive Job (Drilling Navigation and Drilling Solutions Service Provider), Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Accounting & Finance
Industry:
Industrial
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
06 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of one of the world’s leading providers offering complete high accuracy navigation and drilling solutions. Our highly respected client, which has been in operation for more than 40 years, is looking for an accounting and finance management professional with at least three to five years’ experience for the job of Accounting Executive (Accountant), to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia.
Key job responsibilities include:
Fulfill monthly reporting requirements for the divisional accounts department to strict deadlines as determined by corporate, including accounts revenue report and borrowed personnel for the Indonesia district
Prepare sales invoices to be sent to customers, ensuring all appropriate back-up documentation is provided
Check purchase invoices, petty cash and district expense reports, ensuring all appropriate approvals have been obtained
Code income and expenditure as per chart of accounts for the district
Process sales, purchases and journals through dynamics for the district
Ensure revenue and costs are booked on an accurals basis, preparing accruals where necessary
Ensure that monthly accounts package is scanned and sent to division on a timely basis
Perform scheduled reconciliation of balance sheet items including monthly reconciliation of bank accounts
Monitor aged debtors, follow up all overdue invoices and report the status of overdue invoices as required
Administer local tax reporting requirements for VAT, personal and corporate income taxes and licenses
Attend weekly meetings with district ,anager to assist with preparation of monthly sales reporting and budgets
Investigate any queries/discrepancies advised by ditrict manager and division
Discuss ongoing jobs with measurements coordinator and directional drilling manager to assist with financial planning of the departments
Assist in the annual audit process
Perform other relevant duties as requested/required by senior management
Requirements:
Accounting degree (accountant)
At least three to five years’ experience in senior accountant management role
Learns quickly and adapts to new problems and situations
Pursues every job with drive and determination
Use logic to solve problems with effective solutions
Listens and able to communicate effectively with managers and peers, both written and verbally
Able to understand and follow instructions
Presents self with professional appearance and behavior
Ability to multi-task
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.